<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,1295,1464]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[272,404,1297,1320]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Paracoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[272,404,1297,1320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Paracoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is generally included in the tribe Planococcini, diagnosed by the presence of sclerotised anal lobe bars. 
<taxonomicName box="[267,399,1333,1356]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Paracoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[267,399,1333,1356]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Paracoccus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is almost certainly paraphyletic but, as presently understood, has a wide distribution in temperate and tropical regions of the world and now includes about 
<number box="[899,927,1367,1391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="80.0">80</number>
species (
<bibRefCitation author="Williams" box="[1035,1215,1367,1391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="17" refString="Williams, D. J. (2004) Mealybugs of southern Asia. The Natural History Museum &amp; Southdene. SDN. BHD. Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia. [vi], 896 pp." type="book" year="2004">
Williams, 
<number box="[1154,1215,1367,1391]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" value="2004.0">2004</number>
</bibRefCitation>
). Here we describe another species in this genus which is somewhat unusual in possessing enlarged dorsal setae. This suggests some similarity to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sulc" authorityName="Sulc" box="[294,494,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Nipaecoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[294,437,1441,1464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Nipaecoccus</emphasis>
Šulc
</taxonomicName>
but we think it fits better into 
<emphasis box="[834,974,1441,1464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<taxonomicName box="[834,970,1441,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Pseudococcidae" genus="Paracoccus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Paracoccus</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
</paragraph>
